1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:38,360
=Episode 7=

3
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:39,639
My temper?

4
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:41,840
What's wrong with my temper? Seriously?

5
00:01:42,440 --> 00:01:44,189
What kind of attitude was that?

6
00:01:44,190 --> 00:01:46,279
He is definitely in cahoots with Lin Yanping.

7
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:48,790
I wouldn't be surprised
if she hand-picked him herself.

8
00:01:49,470 --> 00:01:51,719
How about you tell the Judge Shen...

9
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:53,200
What Judge Shen?

10
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:55,710
Judge Wang actually
has a decent attitude.

11
00:02:00,750 --> 00:02:03,469
So who ranks higher?
This Wang guy or Judge Shen?

12
00:02:03,470 --> 00:02:05,400
Just stop it. There are cameras.

13
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:13,029
(Enforcement Department Meeting Room)
That's not what I meant.

14
00:02:13,030 --> 00:02:14,720
I was just asking

15
00:02:14,750 --> 00:02:16,440
which of them is older?

16
00:02:17,470 --> 00:02:18,880
This one looks older.

17
00:02:28,790 --> 00:02:29,189
Hello?

18
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:29,839
Wait a second.

19
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:30,880
Don't close it!

20
00:02:31,790 --> 00:02:32,760
Wait up!

21
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:35,350
Hello.

22
00:02:37,510 --> 00:02:39,629
Sir, do you know where Niu Kele lives?

23
00:02:39,630 --> 00:02:41,510
Never seen him. No idea.

24
00:02:41,720 --> 00:02:42,879
How do I get there on the GPS?

25
00:02:42,880 --> 00:02:44,110
Just keep going straight.

26
00:02:44,190 --> 00:02:45,789
You guys are so annoying.

27
00:02:45,790 --> 00:02:47,390
All you do is pressure me!

28
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:50,830
Don't cry. Mommy's here.

29
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:54,789
Hello.

30
00:02:54,790 --> 00:02:56,309
Is Xu Zihan here, please?

31
00:02:56,310 --> 00:02:58,309
Mom, they've filed.

32
00:02:58,310 --> 00:03:00,350
Yang Zixuan is divorcing me.

33
00:03:00,470 --> 00:03:02,040
What? What's going on now?

34
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:05,629
It's that old hag for sure.

35
00:03:05,630 --> 00:03:07,279
If anyone's filing, it's us.

36
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:08,509
Who do they think they are?

37
00:03:08,510 --> 00:03:10,469
Please stay calm.
We're just doing our jobs.

38
00:03:10,470 --> 00:03:11,959
Doing your jobs?

39
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,309
You're clearly in bed with them!

40
00:03:13,310 --> 00:03:14,879
Go back and tell that old hag

41
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:17,670
that my daughter
still has a mother to protect her!

42
00:03:19,510 --> 00:03:23,069
They were looking for parking,
then they're down by the river?

43
00:03:23,070 --> 00:03:25,589
And they say I have a bad temper.
Is this really about my temper?

44
00:03:25,590 --> 00:03:26,719
She's literally pulling a stunt

45
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:28,200
at the court's front door.

46
00:03:28,350 --> 00:03:30,589
This is the Enforcement Department.
Can't we just enforce the order?

47
00:03:30,590 --> 00:03:31,839
Houses, cars, land, bank accounts...

48
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:33,189
You can seize any of those.

49
00:03:33,190 --> 00:03:34,279
But this is a child.

50
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:35,189
How do I enforce that?

51
00:03:35,190 --> 00:03:36,999
Should I cuff him
and drag him here for you?

52
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,320
Would you like that?

53
00:03:38,350 --> 00:03:39,509
Of course not, Judge Wang.

54
00:03:39,510 --> 00:03:41,469
After all, he is the boy's father.

55
00:03:41,470 --> 00:03:43,119
He's just desperate to see his son.

56
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:44,719
But we absolutely
cannot distress the child.

57
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:45,830
Rest assured.

58
00:03:46,070 --> 00:03:47,119
I guess

59
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:47,879
the one who hung up

60
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:49,910
was actually being "polite."

61
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:52,070
Next time this happens,

62
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:54,720
we should send a few burly bailiffs.

63
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:59,320
Le and the others are ordering coffee.

64
00:04:00,030 --> 00:04:02,110
Get me one, too.
I need to take the edge off.

65
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:03,879
They want us to pick them up

66
00:04:03,880 --> 00:04:04,679
on our way back.

67
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:05,719
From where?

68
00:04:05,720 --> 00:04:07,760
That place by the river near the court.

69
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:08,950
Fine.

70
00:04:09,030 --> 00:04:10,200
Zhou Zhou.

71
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:11,399
Look, Daddy's here.

72
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:13,349
He even got you this rocket.

73
00:04:13,350 --> 00:04:14,839
Let's put it together, okay?

74
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:15,719
How about it?

75
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:16,679
No, no, no.

76
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:17,599
A space shuttle?

77
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:19,039
That's not for a kid his age.

78
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:20,679
The parts are too small. He could choke.

79
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,999
Wait, no...

80
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,269
It's not like I got it for you.

81
00:04:24,270 --> 00:04:25,950
Daddy will put it in the car.

82
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:26,999
Zhou Zhou,

83
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,239
I missed you.

84
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:29,880
Let me give you a hug.

85
00:04:32,150 --> 00:04:33,240
What's wrong?

86
00:04:33,950 --> 00:04:36,070
- What are you doing? You made him cry!
- Mommy!

87
00:04:36,390 --> 00:04:37,999
It's okay, sweetie.

88
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,149
Judge, look at this!

89
00:04:39,150 --> 00:04:41,239
- What did you do to him? He's crying!
- I didn't do anything!

90
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,119
I just gave him a hug.

91
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:43,439
Let's just calm down.

92
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:44,439
Give the boy some space.

93
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:45,239
I am calm!

94
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:45,949
At this rate,

95
00:04:45,950 --> 00:04:47,309
he'll forget I'm his father.

96
00:04:47,310 --> 00:04:48,559
My mom's been waiting upstairs.

97
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:49,239
Let him see her.

98
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:50,560
Your mother is here?

99
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:51,919
Come on, son. We're leaving.

100
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:52,749
- Wait!
- Seriously?

101
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:54,359
My mom raised him
from the day he was born.

102
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:55,359
Why can't let her see him?

103
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:56,309
Not a chance.

104
00:04:56,310 --> 00:04:58,069
He had nightmares
for a month after the last time.

105
00:04:58,070 --> 00:04:58,879
Didn't you know that?

106
00:04:58,880 --> 00:04:59,829
My mom got burned

107
00:04:59,830 --> 00:05:01,149
because she was

108
00:05:01,150 --> 00:05:02,479
so distracted missing him!

109
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:03,289
Why are you pushing me?

110
00:05:03,290 --> 00:05:03,999
Don't push me!

111
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,159
I'm taking him right now.

112
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:06,069
- What's going on?
- Let me ask you...

113
00:05:06,070 --> 00:05:07,629
Isn't the boy
supposed to be with me today?

114
00:05:07,630 --> 00:05:10,149
Visitation is only possible
if we respect the child's own wishes.

115
00:05:10,150 --> 00:05:11,189
We are respecting them!

116
00:05:11,190 --> 00:05:12,830
Look at how hard he's crying!

117
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:13,829
Don't you start that car!

118
00:05:13,830 --> 00:05:14,879
Get out!

119
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:15,950
Get out of the car!

120
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:18,919
Get out! Get out!

121
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:20,559
Control your client!

122
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:21,590
Mr. Zhou!

123
00:05:21,630 --> 00:05:23,119
He's mine today!

124
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:23,829
Hurry up!

125
00:05:23,830 --> 00:05:25,479
Lin Yanping, do not drive!

126
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:26,559
Get out! Calm down!

127
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,510
Get out and give me the boy!

128
00:05:28,630 --> 00:05:29,629
Move!

129
00:05:29,630 --> 00:05:30,679
Give him to me!

130
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:32,120
Just run them over!

131
00:05:36,950 --> 00:05:38,479
You're actually trying to run me over?!

132
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:39,999
(Stunt: Do not try this in real life.)

133
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:40,829
Lin Yanping!

134
00:05:40,830 --> 00:05:42,119
Stop! That's dangerous!

135
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:42,709
Lin Yanping!

136
00:05:42,710 --> 00:05:43,880
Stop the car!

137
00:05:45,630 --> 00:05:47,149
Let me see the kid first!

138
00:05:47,150 --> 00:05:48,039
Get out!

139
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:49,200
This is too dangerous!

140
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:19,710
Mr. Zhou!

141
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:20,509
Kill the engine!

142
00:06:20,510 --> 00:06:21,630
Turn it off!

143
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:24,559
Judge Shen!

144
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:25,309
Are you okay?

145
00:06:25,310 --> 00:06:26,510
What happened here?

146
00:06:26,630 --> 00:06:27,749
Everything's gone south.

147
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:29,680
Take the boy and settle him down.

148
00:06:29,710 --> 00:06:31,999
I'll take them back to
the Enforcement Department and explain later.

149
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,120
Lin Yanping!

150
00:06:33,440 --> 00:06:35,120
Were you actually trying to kill me?!

151
00:06:35,630 --> 00:06:36,829
You were too reckless.

152
00:06:36,830 --> 00:06:38,510
You're insane!

153
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:45,830
Ms. Lin.

154
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:46,479
Do you have

155
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:48,710
any idea what you've done today?

156
00:06:50,750 --> 00:06:51,479
Your ex-husband

157
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:53,880
is insisting on filing
an attempted murder charge.

158
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:55,069
Do you realize

159
00:06:55,070 --> 00:06:57,149
what the consequences of that would be?

160
00:06:57,150 --> 00:06:58,559
I just wanted to scare him.

161
00:06:58,560 --> 00:06:59,829
I wasn't even accelerating.

162
00:06:59,830 --> 00:07:00,749
Exactly, Judge Wang.

163
00:07:00,750 --> 00:07:02,359
This doesn't constitute
attempted murder.

164
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:03,709
There was no actual harm done.

165
00:07:03,710 --> 00:07:05,119
She had no malicious intent.

166
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:07,479
We give you our word
that we will fully cooperate

167
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:09,920
with the enforcement process.

168
00:07:09,950 --> 00:07:12,240
As for this afternoon's incident,

169
00:07:12,270 --> 00:07:13,880
we'll need your mediation.

170
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:16,749
How am I supposed to do that?

171
00:07:16,750 --> 00:07:18,389
What is there left to mediate?

172
00:07:18,390 --> 00:07:20,030
Dozens of people saw it!

173
00:07:20,150 --> 00:07:22,240
If Judge Shen's car hadn't
been in the way,

174
00:07:22,310 --> 00:07:24,149
she would've pushed him into traffic!

175
00:07:24,150 --> 00:07:25,439
Please. He's such a coward,

176
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:26,559
he would've jumped off.

177
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:28,069
Without that judge's car in the way,

178
00:07:28,070 --> 00:07:29,470
he would've bolted.

179
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:33,440
You expect me to help
with an attitude like that?

180
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:34,999
No, that's not...

181
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,070
Judge Wang.

182
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:39,439
Look at you.

183
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:41,189
Why would you mention the police report?

184
00:07:41,190 --> 00:07:42,919
At most, she'd get a few days
in detention.

185
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:43,829
The car barely moved.

186
00:07:43,830 --> 00:07:45,439
You could have jumped off at any time.

187
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:46,709
Now this is blowing up,

188
00:07:46,710 --> 00:07:47,949
and it's going to hurt our case

189
00:07:47,950 --> 00:07:49,270
for future visitation.

190
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,359
Wait.

191
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:52,039
I was the one on the hood, not you!

192
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:52,949
From where I stood,

193
00:07:52,950 --> 00:07:54,269
it felt fast!

194
00:07:54,270 --> 00:07:55,309
If I'd hit my head,

195
00:07:55,310 --> 00:07:57,390
I'd be a dead man!

196
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:58,629
Listen.

197
00:07:58,630 --> 00:08:00,309
The whole point was just to scare her.

198
00:08:00,310 --> 00:08:01,309
I had to pressure her.

199
00:08:01,310 --> 00:08:01,879
What if she

200
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:03,470
refuses to let my mom see my son?

201
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,949
I completely understand how you feel.

202
00:08:05,950 --> 00:08:07,559
But scaring her once is enough.

203
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:09,560
But please don't say that in court.

204
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:14,039
Put this one here.

205
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:15,320
Give me a piece.

206
00:08:16,270 --> 00:08:17,560
Good boy.

207
00:08:24,270 --> 00:08:24,919
Zhou Zhou.

208
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:27,800
Finish the rest with the madam, okay?

209
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:30,749
How about this?

210
00:08:30,750 --> 00:08:32,079
I am going

211
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:33,719
to see your parents.

212
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:34,959
I'll be back soon.

213
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:35,749
When I get back,

214
00:08:35,750 --> 00:08:37,800
we'll finish it together, okay?

215
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:39,320
Good boy.

216
00:08:39,630 --> 00:08:40,750
Now...

217
00:08:41,030 --> 00:08:42,359
Keep a close eye on it.

218
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:43,669
Don't let anyone touch it.

219
00:08:43,670 --> 00:08:44,870
Pinky swear?

220
00:08:46,030 --> 00:08:47,320
Now seal the deal.

221
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:48,909
Good boy.

222
00:08:48,910 --> 00:08:50,110
Careful.

223
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:51,710
Watch the rocket.

224
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:53,320
Listen, Lin Yanping.

225
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:55,110
Today,

226
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:58,280
my mom have to see Zhou Zhou.

227
00:08:58,510 --> 00:09:00,479
Believe me, if she doesn't see him,

228
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:01,789
you aren't leaving this court.

229
00:09:01,790 --> 00:09:03,599
I'm taking my son today.

230
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:05,959
You have visitation rights,

231
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:06,909
and I'll cooperate.

232
00:09:06,910 --> 00:09:08,990
But your mother is off-limits.

233
00:09:09,270 --> 00:09:11,389
I'll never let her see Zhou Zhou.

234
00:09:11,390 --> 00:09:13,470
How can you say that?

235
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:14,669
What do you mean

236
00:09:14,670 --> 00:09:16,479
she'll never see him?

237
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:18,239
Sit down. Let's talk calmly.

238
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:19,669
Did you hear that?

239
00:09:19,670 --> 00:09:21,319
Why can't my mother see him?

240
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:22,839
Our issues are between us.

241
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:24,629
From the very beginning,

242
00:09:24,630 --> 00:09:26,509
my mom was always good to you.

243
00:09:26,510 --> 00:09:27,839
She's an old woman now.

244
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:29,149
Why can't she see the boy?

245
00:09:29,150 --> 00:09:30,999
Your mother?
How exactly did she treat me?

246
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:31,749
I owe her nothing!

247
00:09:31,750 --> 00:09:33,119
Don't you dare try to guilt-trip me.

248
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:35,480
(Enforcement Department Meeting Room)
I'm doing this because of her.

249
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:36,839
The boy was terrified!

250
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:37,879
Listen to me.

251
00:09:37,880 --> 00:09:40,029
All I care about is my son's well-being.

252
00:09:40,030 --> 00:09:42,830
I won't let anyone hurt him.
Not even a little.

253
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:44,319
And what about outside?

254
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:45,669
You hit me with your car!

255
00:09:45,670 --> 00:09:47,400
You almost crushed me to death!

256
00:09:47,430 --> 00:09:48,549
I'll tell you what that is.

257
00:09:48,550 --> 00:09:50,440
That's attempted murder!

258
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:51,839
They should arrest you!

259
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:53,269
You belong behind bars!

260
00:09:53,270 --> 00:09:55,319
Fine! Arrest me!
Go ahead and lock me up!

261
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,359
I'll take the prison time!

262
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:58,999
- The boy is the only priority.
- Yes. He is the most important thing.

263
00:09:59,000 --> 00:09:59,719
So lock her up!

264
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:00,909
Then the boy stays with me!

265
00:10:00,910 --> 00:10:02,149
Zhou Xiaofu, how dare you!

266
00:10:02,150 --> 00:10:04,079
Do you really think
I'm still that same pushover?

267
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:05,149
Who's pushing you around?

268
00:10:05,150 --> 00:10:06,879
If he dares
to lay a single finger on my son,

269
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:07,839
I'll show you

270
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:10,029
just how crazy I can get!

271
00:10:10,030 --> 00:10:10,959
Alright, alright!

272
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:12,959
- Don't touch him!
- Did you see that? She hit me!

273
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:14,269
Enough! Calm down!

274
00:10:14,270 --> 00:10:15,359
Stop! This is a court!

275
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:16,549
Did you see her swing at me?

276
00:10:16,550 --> 00:10:17,549
Here, I'm recording this!

277
00:10:17,550 --> 00:10:19,359
Keep filming! I dare you!

278
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:21,520
Keep it civil,
or I'm calling the bailiffs!

279
00:10:23,430 --> 00:10:24,470
Call the police!

280
00:10:24,790 --> 00:10:26,110
I'm calling the police!

281
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,079
Judge Shen.

282
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:31,999
If Mr. Zhou insists on pursuing

283
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,629
attempted murder charges,

284
00:10:33,630 --> 00:10:34,999
I can call the police.

285
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,560
Wait, Judge Shen.

286
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:38,119
I'm begging you, okay?

287
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:39,239
Work with me here.

288
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:41,040
Bring the old lady in from outside.

289
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:46,520
Call the police!

290
00:10:46,630 --> 00:10:47,629
We have to call them!

291
00:10:47,630 --> 00:10:48,479
In broad daylight,

292
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:50,549
she tried to murder her son's father.

293
00:10:50,550 --> 00:10:52,119
This offense has terrible consequences.

294
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:54,160
I'm pushing for ten years behind bars!

295
00:10:54,390 --> 00:10:56,990
That's ridiculous! Ten years for what?

296
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:58,079
Call them then!

297
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:59,719
Go ahead, call the police!

298
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:00,959
She won't let me see the boy.

299
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:01,909
I'm calling the police!

300
00:11:01,910 --> 00:11:03,719
Do it! If you've got the guts, do it!

301
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:04,269
Don't respond.

302
00:11:04,270 --> 00:11:05,959
That was self-defense!

303
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:07,749
Self-defense? You sent him flying!

304
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:08,959
Judge Wang, you saw it yourself.

305
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:10,909
She is openly resisting court orders.

306
00:11:10,910 --> 00:11:12,149
Can we go get the boy now?

307
00:11:12,150 --> 00:11:13,789
You are twisting the facts!

308
00:11:13,790 --> 00:11:14,719
He didn't get sent anywhere.

309
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:16,029
The boy is in the playroom, right?

310
00:11:16,030 --> 00:11:16,509
What?

311
00:11:16,510 --> 00:11:17,789
I'm getting my son!

312
00:11:17,790 --> 00:11:19,029
Don't you touch me!

313
00:11:19,030 --> 00:11:20,719
- Bailiff!
- Judge Wang told me to get him!

314
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:21,119
Bailiff!

315
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:22,229
Judge Wang, do something.

316
00:11:22,230 --> 00:11:22,949
Get off me!

317
00:11:22,950 --> 00:11:24,389
Don't you touch me!
Get out of the way!

318
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:25,669
No one touches my son!

319
00:11:25,670 --> 00:11:26,640
No one!

320
00:11:27,390 --> 00:11:28,599
- What are you doing?
- Judge Wang, what is the meaning of this?

321
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,719
You can't arrest me!

322
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:30,629
I must care for the boy.

323
00:11:30,630 --> 00:11:31,839
Stop!

324
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:32,520
Let her go!

325
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:34,479
- Ma'am, you can't come in!
- Let her go!

326
00:11:34,480 --> 00:11:36,629
Let her go! Let her go!

327
00:11:36,630 --> 00:11:37,920
- Please, let her go!
- You can't enter!

328
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,350
Judge.

329
00:11:44,390 --> 00:11:46,990
Please have mercy on my daughter-in-law.

330
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:50,040
She isn't a bad person.

331
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:53,050
I mean it.

332
00:11:55,660 --> 00:11:56,710
My son...

333
00:11:57,380 --> 00:11:59,680
They were both so busy with work.

334
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:01,110
The constant fighting

335
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:02,870
just couldn't make it work.

336
00:12:03,630 --> 00:12:05,680
But she is a wonderful mother.

337
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:09,070
The way she cares for my grandson
is beyond words.

338
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:12,479
Ever since he was a baby,

339
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:14,359
I helped look after him.

340
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:15,590
But me...

341
00:12:15,630 --> 00:12:16,959
I'm old and my eyes are failing.

342
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:19,640
I've made my share of mistakes.

343
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:21,079
But she...

344
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:23,920
She never once said a bad word to me.

345
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:27,680
After the divorce,

346
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:29,629
she didn't complain once.

347
00:12:29,630 --> 00:12:31,549
She raised that child all on her own.

348
00:12:31,550 --> 00:12:33,230
It hasn't been easy for her.

349
00:12:34,750 --> 00:12:37,520
If you take her away now,

350
00:12:39,030 --> 00:12:43,160
how is that poor boy
supposed to survive?

351
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:50,870
I am nothing but old bones now.

352
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:53,400
I don't have many years left anyway.

353
00:12:54,030 --> 00:12:57,079
Zhou Zhou would be
just fine even without me.

354
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:58,560
Right?

355
00:12:59,030 --> 00:13:01,280
But if he loses his mother,

356
00:13:01,670 --> 00:13:04,750
his entire life will be ruined.

357
00:13:09,670 --> 00:13:11,789
I don't need to see
my grandson anymore, okay?

358
00:13:11,790 --> 00:13:13,110
I'll stop.

359
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:13,669
Mom!

360
00:13:13,670 --> 00:13:15,160
I won't see Zhou Zhou again.

361
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:16,389
Is that enough?

362
00:13:16,390 --> 00:13:17,680
Mom.

363
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:19,959
- Please. Just have a heart and let her go.
- Mom...

364
00:13:19,960 --> 00:13:21,199
Let her go home, please.

365
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:23,560
Mom, it's all my fault.

366
00:13:23,670 --> 00:13:25,830
I know you've always been good to me.

367
00:13:25,910 --> 00:13:28,079
I only did this
to get back at Zhou Xiaofu.

368
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:30,070
I wanted to keep the boy from him.

369
00:13:30,390 --> 00:13:32,590
I wanted to use the child
to make him crawl.

370
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:34,749
But I never meant to hurt you.

371
00:13:34,750 --> 00:13:37,509
I didn't really mean to keep him
from you forever.

372
00:13:37,510 --> 00:13:39,509
Once the marks on your face heal,

373
00:13:39,510 --> 00:13:40,839
and Zhou Zhou isn't scared anymore,

374
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:43,440
I promise I'll bring him to you myself.

375
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:45,509
Mom, I'm so sorry.

376
00:13:45,510 --> 00:13:46,879
This is all on me.

377
00:13:46,880 --> 00:13:49,230
Zhou Zhou is my whole world.

378
00:13:49,390 --> 00:13:52,280
I couldn't stand
to see him suffer at all.

379
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:55,350
But...

380
00:13:55,430 --> 00:13:57,320
I completely forgot...

381
00:13:57,600 --> 00:14:00,070
that he is your world, too.

382
00:14:00,550 --> 00:14:01,560
Mom...

383
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:03,320
I'm so sorry, Mom.

384
00:14:04,030 --> 00:14:05,950
I'm so, so sorry.

385
00:14:06,430 --> 00:14:08,110
Forgive me, Mom.

386
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:12,590
Mom...

387
00:14:32,670 --> 00:14:33,870
Thank you.

388
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:38,590
Grandma, did you miss me?

389
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:40,909
I did. Grandma missed you so much.

390
00:14:40,910 --> 00:14:41,669
Hold onto Grandma.

391
00:14:41,670 --> 00:14:42,920
Granny.

392
00:14:43,510 --> 00:14:45,200
Grandma, look.

393
00:14:46,550 --> 00:14:48,280
Thank you, thank you.

394
00:14:48,510 --> 00:14:50,029
Zhou Zhou, look.

395
00:14:50,030 --> 00:14:52,040
See what Grandma brought for you?

396
00:14:52,630 --> 00:14:53,750
Look.

397
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:56,920
- Your favorite sesame candy.
- And Mommy's favorite crackers.

398
00:14:57,320 --> 00:14:58,429
Right?

399
00:14:58,430 --> 00:14:58,789
Here.

400
00:14:58,790 --> 00:15:00,359
- Go ahead, have one.
- Go on.

401
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:02,119
Grandma will pick a big one for you.

402
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:02,599
Eat up.

403
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:03,509
Thanks, Mom.

404
00:15:03,510 --> 00:15:04,999
I can't believe you brought candy.

405
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:06,200
You should eat too.

406
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:08,070
Thank you, Grandma.

407
00:15:08,510 --> 00:15:09,509
(When two strangers)

408
00:15:09,510 --> 00:15:11,389
(meet through the gravity of love)

409
00:15:11,390 --> 00:15:13,920
(to build a universe called home,)

410
00:15:14,510 --> 00:15:15,319
(they begin)

411
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:17,269
(to weave shared interests)

412
00:15:17,270 --> 00:15:18,999
(and accumulate common assets)

413
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,560
(as worldly symbols of their bond.)

414
00:15:21,430 --> 00:15:22,230
(However,)

415
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:24,110
(when feelings wither,)

416
00:15:24,430 --> 00:15:27,669
(the scales of justice
can weigh property)

417
00:15:27,670 --> 00:15:29,520
(and sever debt entanglements,)

418
00:15:29,910 --> 00:15:31,029
(but they struggle to measure)

419
00:15:31,030 --> 00:15:33,830
(the invisible, heavier weight of)

420
00:15:34,320 --> 00:15:35,440
(family bonds.)

421
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,999
(Even if visitation rights are set)

422
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:39,640
(in black and white on a judgment,)

423
00:15:39,790 --> 00:15:42,560
(a child, the subject of that visit,)

424
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:44,950
(is not a number on a ledger.)

425
00:15:45,270 --> 00:15:47,629
(You cannot simply
reclaim or enforce love)

426
00:15:47,630 --> 00:15:49,640
(based on the clauses of a court order.)

427
00:15:50,510 --> 00:15:51,749
(Family court judges)

428
00:15:51,750 --> 00:15:54,350
(are far from
mechanical legal enforcers.)

429
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:58,160
(They deal not
with black-and-white truth,)

430
00:15:58,480 --> 00:16:00,230
(but with an emotional fog)

431
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:03,040
(where every side has its own reason.)

432
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:05,389
(This requires a judge to have)

433
00:16:05,390 --> 00:16:07,749
(both a keen eye and a merciful heart,)

434
00:16:07,750 --> 00:16:10,160
(performing a sort of soul archaeology.)

435
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:12,199
(Excavating forgotten care)

436
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:14,350
(from the ruins of complaints,)

437
00:16:14,790 --> 00:16:16,680
(and salvaging original tenderness)

438
00:16:16,960 --> 00:16:19,040
(from the weight of accusations.)

439
00:16:36,880 --> 00:16:39,269
Doing your "anger-release"
routine again?

440
00:16:39,270 --> 00:16:40,629
It's not for anger today.

441
00:16:40,630 --> 00:16:42,029
I've upgraded.

442
00:16:42,030 --> 00:16:42,879
This one?

443
00:16:42,880 --> 00:16:45,590
It's my "soothe-my-
shattered-nerves" routine.

444
00:16:47,550 --> 00:16:48,750
Fair enough.

445
00:16:49,030 --> 00:16:52,830
You guys pulled off that
"Fast & Furious" stunt today.

446
00:16:53,550 --> 00:16:55,520
Do you think "Machine Shen"

447
00:16:55,910 --> 00:16:57,749
knew that couple

448
00:16:57,750 --> 00:16:59,429
would drive right onto the main road,

449
00:16:59,430 --> 00:17:01,040
so he blocked them on purpose?

450
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:02,629
What if they'd actually crashed?

451
00:17:02,630 --> 00:17:04,079
He definitely did it on purpose.

452
00:17:04,080 --> 00:17:05,709
But according to Judge Wang,

453
00:17:05,710 --> 00:17:06,949
a crash was never in the cards.

454
00:17:06,950 --> 00:17:08,949
Apparently, he was once

455
00:17:08,950 --> 00:17:11,629
an amateur go-kart
champion or something.

456
00:17:11,630 --> 00:17:13,440
He had everything under control.

457
00:17:13,520 --> 00:17:15,200
I see.

458
00:17:15,390 --> 00:17:17,359
No wonder he didn't
last in the Family Court.

459
00:17:17,360 --> 00:17:19,519
He's just a man of brawn.

460
00:17:19,520 --> 00:17:20,989
"Brawn"?

461
00:17:20,990 --> 00:17:22,880
I don't think that's quite right.

462
00:17:23,230 --> 00:17:23,949
Honestly,

463
00:17:23,950 --> 00:17:26,120
he really impressed me today.

464
00:17:26,470 --> 00:17:27,950
The way he

465
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:30,510
handled things was quite clever.

466
00:17:31,910 --> 00:17:34,510
What was so clever about it?

467
00:17:35,390 --> 00:17:37,640
He identified the heart of the issue.

468
00:17:37,710 --> 00:17:38,949
Understand human nature,

469
00:17:38,950 --> 00:17:40,710
and you have the key to everything.

470
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:42,990
We're talking human nature now?

471
00:17:46,630 --> 00:17:47,880
I get it.

472
00:17:48,520 --> 00:17:50,709
Instead of just treating the symptoms,

473
00:17:50,710 --> 00:17:53,440
he went for the root cause, right?

474
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:55,030
Exactly.

475
00:17:55,390 --> 00:17:56,429
Actually, that couple

476
00:17:56,430 --> 00:17:58,319
didn't even have any deep-seated hatred.

477
00:17:58,320 --> 00:17:59,519
They weren't estranged.

478
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:01,429
They didn't want each other in jail.

479
00:18:01,430 --> 00:18:03,519
They just said those things
in the heat of the moment.

480
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:04,599
They were flared up.

481
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:06,880
They were just trying
to outdo each other.

482
00:18:09,760 --> 00:18:11,149
To put it simply,

483
00:18:11,150 --> 00:18:12,880
it's just a matter of resentment.

484
00:18:13,230 --> 00:18:15,599
Feeling like
their best years were wasted.

485
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:16,519
Which is why

486
00:18:16,520 --> 00:18:19,310
Mr. Zhou's mother was
the key to everything.

487
00:18:19,360 --> 00:18:21,200
She was the weak link in the chain.

488
00:18:21,320 --> 00:18:22,079
Shen Xiezhi

489
00:18:22,080 --> 00:18:24,550
happened to catch onto that.

490
00:18:24,840 --> 00:18:25,799
As I said,

491
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:27,680
the guy has a few tricks up his sleeve.

492
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:45,270
- What was that for?
- What's on your mind?

493
00:18:45,430 --> 00:18:48,310
Falling for Machine Shen's charms?

494
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:50,950
Falling for what? Please.

495
00:18:51,040 --> 00:18:53,389
Impressed by his IQ. What of it?

496
00:18:53,390 --> 00:18:54,950
What are you thinking?

497
00:18:55,520 --> 00:18:56,920
Speaking of IQ,

498
00:18:56,990 --> 00:18:58,359
he should be impressed by mine.

499
00:18:58,360 --> 00:19:00,160
Right, right. Help me!

500
00:19:02,520 --> 00:19:03,039
I'm telling you,

501
00:19:03,040 --> 00:19:04,750
I'm still the smarter one here.

502
00:19:09,630 --> 00:19:12,389
(Fourth Court: In Session)
This is no way to live!

503
00:19:12,390 --> 00:19:13,599
(Hearing in progress)
That's enough.

504
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:15,799
(Family Court)
The court has noted the final requests

505
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:17,149
of the plaintiff and the defendant.

506
00:19:17,150 --> 00:19:19,680
Next, we will conduct
a comprehensive evaluation

507
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:22,229
(Qingcheng District People's Court)
of the evidence and the arguments.

508
00:19:22,230 --> 00:19:23,759
A ruling will be announced

509
00:19:23,760 --> 00:19:25,189
at a later date.

510
00:19:25,190 --> 00:19:26,470
Adjourned.

511
00:19:28,080 --> 00:19:29,519
Just wait till I get my hands on you!

512
00:19:29,520 --> 00:19:30,389
What are you doing?

513
00:19:30,390 --> 00:19:31,669
(Fourth Court: Angle 1)

514
00:19:31,670 --> 00:19:32,359
Liu Jingang!

515
00:19:32,360 --> 00:19:33,750
I need protection!

516
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:34,949
My brother-in-law here

517
00:19:34,950 --> 00:19:36,270
throws nasty punches.

518
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:37,839
My last fracture just healed.

519
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:38,879
If I break anything else,

520
00:19:38,880 --> 00:19:40,230
there'll be no fixing it!

521
00:19:40,430 --> 00:19:41,680
Put that down!

522
00:19:43,230 --> 00:19:44,599
Who did I do this for?

523
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:46,279
I went through all of this for you!

524
00:19:46,280 --> 00:19:47,879
You said you liked beautiful women!

525
00:19:47,880 --> 00:19:49,229
Fine! So I got surgery!

526
00:19:49,230 --> 00:19:50,389
Four times under the knife!

527
00:19:50,390 --> 00:19:52,429
Now you say you liked the "original"?

528
00:19:52,430 --> 00:19:53,519
My face is ruined,

529
00:19:53,520 --> 00:19:55,229
and my job is gone.

530
00:19:55,230 --> 00:19:56,389
Even my mother and child

531
00:19:56,390 --> 00:19:57,359
have abandoned me!

532
00:19:57,360 --> 00:19:59,279
Judge, if you grant this divorce,

533
00:19:59,280 --> 00:20:01,439
I'll jump right off this building!

534
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:02,319
(Third Court: Angle 1)

535
00:20:02,320 --> 00:20:03,119
What are you doing?

536
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:03,839
Defendant, stay calm!

537
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:05,310
Calm down, please!

538
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:13,229
Judge Shen.

539
00:20:13,230 --> 00:20:14,799
Files for the upcoming mediation

540
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:16,909
regarding Feng Lianshan's suit
for filial support.

541
00:20:16,910 --> 00:20:18,079
Would you like to review them?

542
00:20:18,080 --> 00:20:19,119
I remember the details.

543
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:20,949
Check if Ms. Shu needs to see them.

544
00:20:20,950 --> 00:20:23,270
Ms. Shu is still tied up in a meeting.

545
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:25,989
Then ask her if she's okay

546
00:20:25,990 --> 00:20:27,909
with me leading the mediation for now.

547
00:20:27,910 --> 00:20:29,790
You? Are you sure?

548
00:20:30,150 --> 00:20:30,879
Why?

549
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:32,470
It's that Feng Shengli.

550
00:20:32,600 --> 00:20:33,429
Without those robes,

551
00:20:33,430 --> 00:20:35,310
you'd actually punch him.

552
00:20:36,520 --> 00:20:38,189
(Sixth Court: In Session)
I'm telling you,

553
00:20:38,190 --> 00:20:39,790
ever since he was a kid,

554
00:20:40,120 --> 00:20:41,550
this entire family

555
00:20:41,630 --> 00:20:43,950
gave him the best of everything!

556
00:20:44,800 --> 00:20:46,469
When he wanted meat as a child,

557
00:20:46,470 --> 00:20:47,319
Dad would

558
00:20:47,320 --> 00:20:49,279
hunt a rabbit just for him.

559
00:20:49,280 --> 00:20:50,429
When he went to boarding school,

560
00:20:50,430 --> 00:20:52,389
we all survived on smaller rations

561
00:20:52,390 --> 00:20:54,079
to carry food and rice miles to him!

562
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:55,400
Remember that?

563
00:20:55,760 --> 00:20:57,189
Then, he wanted to buy a house.

564
00:20:57,190 --> 00:20:58,629
Dad was over sixty,

565
00:20:58,630 --> 00:21:01,270
but he hauled feed at the pig farm
just for extra cash!

566
00:21:01,430 --> 00:21:02,559
He worked himself

567
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:04,039
to death for you!

568
00:21:04,040 --> 00:21:05,079
Look, Brother.

569
00:21:05,080 --> 00:21:06,359
Do you know how to raise pigs?

570
00:21:06,360 --> 00:21:08,039
You feed the one that fattens up fastest

571
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:09,559
the absolute best quality food,

572
00:21:09,560 --> 00:21:11,519
so you can fetch a higher price later.

573
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:13,229
At the end of the day,
it's just a matter

574
00:21:13,230 --> 00:21:14,799
of basic Return on Investment.

575
00:21:14,800 --> 00:21:15,799
Why you...

576
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:16,839
How dare you?

577
00:21:16,840 --> 00:21:18,189
Say that again!

578
00:21:18,190 --> 00:21:19,039
I dare you!

579
00:21:19,040 --> 00:21:20,429
Sit down! Everyone, please sit!

580
00:21:20,430 --> 00:21:21,950
Brother, listen to me.

581
00:21:22,080 --> 00:21:23,149
We are just

582
00:21:23,150 --> 00:21:24,559
livestock he raised.

583
00:21:24,560 --> 00:21:25,949
Except some are for meat,

584
00:21:25,950 --> 00:21:27,429
some are for profit,

585
00:21:27,430 --> 00:21:30,149
and some actually cost more in feed
than they're worth.

586
00:21:30,150 --> 00:21:31,319
Feng Shengli!

587
00:21:31,320 --> 00:21:32,599
You ungrateful scoundrel!

588
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:34,149
Dad raised you for nothing!

589
00:21:34,150 --> 00:21:35,389
Ms. Feng, please calm down.

590
00:21:35,390 --> 00:21:36,799
If livestock can be sold for profit,

591
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:38,429
then I fetch the highest price.

592
00:21:38,430 --> 00:21:39,709
Isn't that better than being eaten?

593
00:21:39,710 --> 00:21:40,949
Look at the big picture.

594
00:21:40,950 --> 00:21:42,559
Mr. Feng, that's enough.

595
00:21:42,560 --> 00:21:44,319
We agreed to focus on the medical bills.

596
00:21:44,320 --> 00:21:46,310
Let's avoid the hurtful comments.

597
00:21:47,680 --> 00:21:49,560
(Third Court: In Session)

598
00:21:50,880 --> 00:21:52,080
What an ingrate.

599
00:21:52,470 --> 00:21:53,079
I...

600
00:21:53,080 --> 00:21:54,279
He is unbelievable!

601
00:21:54,280 --> 00:21:55,559
Don't you agree?

602
00:21:55,560 --> 00:21:56,469
Please, take a breath.

603
00:21:56,470 --> 00:21:58,229
Supporting parents is
every child's duty.

604
00:21:58,230 --> 00:21:59,709
Fine, fine.

605
00:21:59,710 --> 00:22:01,119
I'm done talking.

606
00:22:01,120 --> 00:22:01,799
But listen up,

607
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:03,160
I've done my research.

608
00:22:03,360 --> 00:22:04,709
At a company like his,

609
00:22:04,710 --> 00:22:05,519
someone in his position

610
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:07,990
makes 200 to 300 thousand a year!

611
00:22:08,150 --> 00:22:09,279
As his older siblings,

612
00:22:09,280 --> 00:22:11,640
we've never benefited from his success.

613
00:22:11,760 --> 00:22:14,469
And my Dad certainly isn't
living the high life.

614
00:22:14,470 --> 00:22:15,949
Asking him for medical expenses

615
00:22:15,950 --> 00:22:17,230
isn't unreasonable, is it?

616
00:22:17,390 --> 00:22:18,469
All that money

617
00:22:18,470 --> 00:22:20,079
we spent on his education back then

618
00:22:20,080 --> 00:22:22,840
would've been worth a fortune
had we invested in real estate instead!

619
00:22:23,040 --> 00:22:24,629
We aren't asking for much.

620
00:22:24,630 --> 00:22:25,879
We just want him

621
00:22:25,880 --> 00:22:27,879
to pay that money back with interest.

622
00:22:27,880 --> 00:22:29,469
Is that too much to ask, Judge?

623
00:22:29,470 --> 00:22:30,949
I'm not the judge.

624
00:22:30,950 --> 00:22:32,879
The judge will base
the ruling on actual costs

625
00:22:32,880 --> 00:22:34,920
and the financial capacity
of each child.

626
00:22:36,990 --> 00:22:38,629
Ma'am, please don't be sad.

627
00:22:38,630 --> 00:22:39,989
Try to stay calm.

628
00:22:39,990 --> 00:22:42,039
No, listen to me.

629
00:22:42,040 --> 00:22:43,359
My brother

630
00:22:43,360 --> 00:22:44,879
wasn't always like this.

631
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:46,319
The year he started working,

632
00:22:46,320 --> 00:22:47,429
he even told us

633
00:22:47,430 --> 00:22:49,400
to make sure our kids studied hard.

634
00:22:49,470 --> 00:22:51,039
He said if they went
to college in Tianhai,

635
00:22:51,040 --> 00:22:52,680
he'd pay their tuition.

636
00:22:54,120 --> 00:22:55,759
He must be in a relationship.

637
00:22:55,760 --> 00:22:57,790
Someone must be poisoning his mind.

638
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:00,599
You should look into it.

639
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:01,920
Please find out the truth.

640
00:23:02,710 --> 00:23:03,990
Mr. Feng.

641
00:23:04,880 --> 00:23:06,799
I understand that making it on your own

642
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:08,759
in a big city is no small feat.

643
00:23:08,760 --> 00:23:09,559
I also realize

644
00:23:09,560 --> 00:23:10,879
the immense pressure you're under

645
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:13,629
to change your family's entire future.

646
00:23:13,630 --> 00:23:15,880
It certainly isn't fair to you.

647
00:23:16,230 --> 00:23:17,510
However,

648
00:23:17,950 --> 00:23:20,039
our parents gave us life and raised us.

649
00:23:20,040 --> 00:23:22,310
It's only right to give something back.

650
00:23:23,670 --> 00:23:25,920
Are you from out of town? A country boy?

651
00:23:26,080 --> 00:23:26,949
I'm a local.

652
00:23:26,950 --> 00:23:28,750
Then your parents rely on you?

653
00:23:29,230 --> 00:23:30,510
They're unemployed too?

654
00:23:31,190 --> 00:23:32,189
At the moment, no.

655
00:23:32,190 --> 00:23:33,640
Then you're just like me.

656
00:23:33,990 --> 00:23:35,599
Ten years of work for a down payment,

657
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:37,359
and a massive mortgage every month?

658
00:23:37,360 --> 00:23:38,389
Mr. Feng,

659
00:23:38,390 --> 00:23:39,759
I don't believe that someone

660
00:23:39,760 --> 00:23:41,759
must experience
every hardship themselves

661
00:23:41,760 --> 00:23:43,550
just to show empathy to others.

662
00:23:43,560 --> 00:23:45,319
Nor do I believe one has to experience

663
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:46,759
every moral conflict

664
00:23:46,760 --> 00:23:49,559
to make a fair and correct judgment.

665
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:51,189
Coming back to the matter at hand.

666
00:23:51,190 --> 00:23:52,550
Ethically,

667
00:23:52,670 --> 00:23:53,909
even nature teaches us

668
00:23:53,910 --> 00:23:55,310
to care for those who cared for us.

669
00:23:55,320 --> 00:23:56,359
Legally,

670
00:23:56,360 --> 00:23:58,990
children have a clear duty
to support their parents.

671
00:23:59,670 --> 00:24:01,270
Then let me tell you this.

672
00:24:01,280 --> 00:24:03,080
Unless you've walked in my shoes,

673
00:24:03,120 --> 00:24:04,880
don't tell me how to be kind.

674
00:24:06,150 --> 00:24:07,229
True empathy

675
00:24:07,230 --> 00:24:09,680
simply does not exist.

676
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:11,710
Do your parents
even need your support?

677
00:24:12,710 --> 00:24:13,750
No.

678
00:24:14,320 --> 00:24:15,790
You don't even have a girlfriend,

679
00:24:15,840 --> 00:24:17,989
yet they've got a car
and a house waiting for you.

680
00:24:17,990 --> 00:24:19,799
Did they book the flights and hotels

681
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:21,550
for your honeymoon too?

682
00:24:22,710 --> 00:24:24,030
You wouldn't understand.

683
00:24:24,560 --> 00:24:25,949
Have you ever felt

684
00:24:25,950 --> 00:24:27,230
the desperation of my life?

685
00:24:27,520 --> 00:24:31,030
The feeling of working yourself
to death just for a chance?

686
00:24:31,280 --> 00:24:33,709
What right do you have
to lecture me like this?

687
00:24:33,710 --> 00:24:35,469
Please stop making assumptions

688
00:24:35,470 --> 00:24:37,079
about my personal background.

689
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:39,510
Everyone has their own cross to bear.

690
00:24:39,630 --> 00:24:42,160
I also fought for every step
that brought me here.

691
00:24:45,710 --> 00:24:46,909
My point is,

692
00:24:46,910 --> 00:24:48,989
if you refuse mediation,
that's your choice.

693
00:24:48,990 --> 00:24:50,469
But once we go to trial,

694
00:24:50,470 --> 00:24:51,879
you will be held accountable

695
00:24:51,880 --> 00:24:52,909
for every legal obligation.

696
00:24:52,910 --> 00:24:54,909
And you'll lose

697
00:24:54,910 --> 00:24:55,989
your parents,

698
00:24:55,990 --> 00:24:57,790
and the bond you have
with your siblings.

699
00:24:58,280 --> 00:24:59,680
"Family bond"?

700
00:25:00,880 --> 00:25:02,119
That's a luxury

701
00:25:02,120 --> 00:25:04,230
reserved for happy families.

702
00:25:04,430 --> 00:25:06,920
I don't have the luxury
of caring about others.

703
00:25:07,280 --> 00:25:08,550
I'm better off without it.

704
00:25:13,190 --> 00:25:16,470
Ms. Qin here,
outside Qingcheng Court,

705
00:25:16,520 --> 00:25:18,669
with a serious warning for everyone.

706
00:25:18,670 --> 00:25:20,470
Beware the visitation agreement trap.

707
00:25:20,560 --> 00:25:23,039
Just because a burger joint
closed and moved,

708
00:25:23,040 --> 00:25:24,879
a father has been blocked

709
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:26,550
from seeing his own son.

710
00:25:26,950 --> 00:25:28,989
Once love turns sour,
every move is calculated.

711
00:25:28,990 --> 00:25:30,160
(Ms. Liu)

712
00:25:36,010 --> 00:25:37,440
Hello, Ms. Liu.

713
00:25:38,520 --> 00:25:40,990
I've already arrived at Qingcheng Court.

714
00:25:42,190 --> 00:25:43,629
How much longer until you're here?

715
00:25:43,630 --> 00:25:45,840
Yes, that's right.
You'll have to go through security.

716
00:25:47,710 --> 00:25:50,270
Okay. I'll be here waiting for you.

717
00:25:59,280 --> 00:26:02,750
Years of marriage sour in an instant.

718
00:26:02,910 --> 00:26:04,550
Every move is calculated.

719
00:26:04,710 --> 00:26:05,840
One...

720
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:12,799
- Careful, Brother. Easy now.
- How is he?

721
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:14,030
Well?

722
00:26:15,190 --> 00:26:17,149
Slowly, slowly. Good.

723
00:26:17,150 --> 00:26:18,039
Let's go.

724
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:19,119
Take it easy.

725
00:26:19,120 --> 00:26:20,310
Easy.

726
00:26:21,230 --> 00:26:24,030
Slowly. There we go.

727
00:26:24,280 --> 00:26:25,230
Good.

728
00:26:27,950 --> 00:26:29,600
Thank you.

729
00:26:29,670 --> 00:26:30,750
Alright.

730
00:26:38,390 --> 00:26:40,440
Judge Shen, we're here.

731
00:26:40,760 --> 00:26:42,230
Yes, we've arrived.

732
00:26:53,990 --> 00:26:56,270
I thought you said he'd recovered?

733
00:26:56,670 --> 00:26:58,669
You can't be serious.

734
00:26:58,670 --> 00:26:59,799
He has.

735
00:26:59,800 --> 00:27:02,359
This is as good as it gets for him.

736
00:27:02,360 --> 00:27:03,039
Yes.

737
00:27:03,040 --> 00:27:04,840
His best?

738
00:27:06,190 --> 00:27:07,469
Does none of this

739
00:27:07,470 --> 00:27:08,669
seem wrong to you three?

740
00:27:08,670 --> 00:27:10,119
Of course it's wrong.

741
00:27:10,120 --> 00:27:11,949
That's why we're here to settle this.

742
00:27:11,950 --> 00:27:13,880
He's staying with me from now on.

743
00:27:14,990 --> 00:27:17,120
I've suffered enough.

744
00:27:21,800 --> 00:27:22,949
Mr. Yao.

745
00:27:22,950 --> 00:27:24,880
Regarding the matter of guardianship,

746
00:27:25,470 --> 00:27:27,550
what are your personal wishes?

747
00:27:31,990 --> 00:27:33,230
Brother.

748
00:27:34,600 --> 00:27:35,429
Judge,

749
00:27:35,430 --> 00:27:38,360
if you want to hear his honest opinion,

750
00:27:38,840 --> 00:27:40,389
ask those two to step out.

751
00:27:40,390 --> 00:27:41,189
Why is that?

752
00:27:41,190 --> 00:27:42,079
Excuse me?

753
00:27:42,080 --> 00:27:44,470
He just wants to hear the truth.

754
00:27:53,470 --> 00:27:54,750
Ms. Liu,

755
00:27:54,910 --> 00:27:57,200
you still seem a bit nervous.

756
00:27:59,360 --> 00:28:01,360
I really shouldn't have come.

757
00:28:01,630 --> 00:28:03,680
Children have jobs.

758
00:28:04,040 --> 00:28:05,680
They're respectable people.

759
00:28:06,190 --> 00:28:07,550
Coming here

760
00:28:07,710 --> 00:28:09,750
is going to ruin them.

761
00:28:10,670 --> 00:28:11,909
That's not true.

762
00:28:11,910 --> 00:28:13,079
Ms. Liu,

763
00:28:13,080 --> 00:28:14,790
they're all adults now.

764
00:28:14,910 --> 00:28:16,920
They have to answer
for their own actions.

765
00:28:19,080 --> 00:28:20,840
Try not to overthink it.

766
00:28:21,900 --> 00:28:23,079
(Qingcheng District People's Court)

767
00:28:23,080 --> 00:28:24,599
My husband and I

768
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:26,519
were married for over thirty years.

769
00:28:26,520 --> 00:28:28,229
(Family Court)

770
00:28:28,230 --> 00:28:29,950
We were always very happy together.

771
00:28:30,360 --> 00:28:32,640
We never once had an argument.

772
00:28:33,080 --> 00:28:34,359
I still remember

773
00:28:34,360 --> 00:28:36,710
the first day I entered their home.

774
00:28:36,760 --> 00:28:38,680
Both children ran straight toward me,

775
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:41,310
calling me "Mom."

776
00:28:42,840 --> 00:28:44,550
In that moment,

777
00:28:45,430 --> 00:28:46,429
I was

778
00:28:46,430 --> 00:28:48,510
deeply moved.

779
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:52,559
Every worry I had just vanished.

780
00:28:52,560 --> 00:28:54,200
I thought to myself,

781
00:28:55,040 --> 00:28:57,200
"These are my own children."

782
00:28:57,280 --> 00:28:58,950
And I made a silent vow

783
00:28:59,800 --> 00:29:02,990
to raise them right, no matter what.

784
00:29:09,320 --> 00:29:10,550
Because of that,

785
00:29:10,760 --> 00:29:12,990
I never had children of my own.

786
00:29:14,040 --> 00:29:15,360
As time went by,

787
00:29:16,040 --> 00:29:18,080
the children grew up.

788
00:29:18,470 --> 00:29:20,470
They started families of their own

789
00:29:21,710 --> 00:29:23,790
and eventually had their own kids.

790
00:29:24,560 --> 00:29:25,629
Back then,

791
00:29:25,630 --> 00:29:27,880
they visited us every single week.

792
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:30,360
And the little ones

793
00:29:30,390 --> 00:29:32,189
were always so sweet

794
00:29:32,190 --> 00:29:35,160
when they called me "Grandma."

795
00:29:37,230 --> 00:29:39,030
But then, just last month,

796
00:29:39,670 --> 00:29:42,279
my husband passed away quite suddenly.

797
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:44,120
And I don't know why,

798
00:29:44,600 --> 00:29:46,310
but ever since then,

799
00:29:46,840 --> 00:29:48,710
the children refuse to see me at all.

800
00:29:50,430 --> 00:29:51,629
You're just the nanny.

801
00:29:51,630 --> 00:29:52,879
Stop meddling, okay?

802
00:29:52,880 --> 00:29:54,469
My dad hates you. He can't stand you.

803
00:29:54,470 --> 00:29:55,319
You know that, right?

804
00:29:55,320 --> 00:29:56,119
Hand it over.

805
00:29:56,120 --> 00:29:56,799
Hand what over?

806
00:29:56,800 --> 00:29:57,599
The pension card.

807
00:29:57,600 --> 00:29:58,559
So you've got the card?

808
00:29:58,560 --> 00:30:00,429
Everyone looks like
a payroll card to you.

809
00:30:00,430 --> 00:30:02,759
So? Is it with you or her?

810
00:30:02,760 --> 00:30:06,200
(Third Court)

811
00:30:06,380 --> 00:30:09,680
Go ask your father.

812
00:30:12,390 --> 00:30:13,389
Judge Shen.

813
00:30:13,390 --> 00:30:14,319
What did my dad say?

814
00:30:14,320 --> 00:30:14,839
Yeah, exactly.

815
00:30:14,840 --> 00:30:16,470
What did he say?

816
00:30:17,120 --> 00:30:18,149
Keep going.

817
00:30:18,150 --> 00:30:19,189
Don't stop now.

818
00:30:19,190 --> 00:30:20,510
Why don't you use this energy

819
00:30:20,600 --> 00:30:21,950
to take care of him.

820
00:30:26,950 --> 00:30:28,229
Are we finished?

821
00:30:28,230 --> 00:30:29,079
Finished?

822
00:30:29,080 --> 00:30:30,550
Then it's my turn to speak.

823
00:30:31,560 --> 00:30:32,989
I think it's pretty clear

824
00:30:32,990 --> 00:30:34,599
that the odds of you all

825
00:30:34,600 --> 00:30:36,160
caring for Mr. Yao are slim.

826
00:30:36,280 --> 00:30:37,669
So, let's discuss

827
00:30:37,670 --> 00:30:39,920
the possibility of a rotating schedule.

828
00:30:40,390 --> 00:30:40,839
Fine.

829
00:30:40,840 --> 00:30:41,429
Alright?

830
00:30:41,430 --> 00:30:42,359
I'll take

831
00:30:42,360 --> 00:30:43,759
the first four months.

832
00:30:43,760 --> 00:30:44,669
Because I know

833
00:30:44,670 --> 00:30:47,119
his habits and his routine

834
00:30:47,120 --> 00:30:48,599
better than anyone.

835
00:30:48,600 --> 00:30:51,200
Oh, please. You don't know anything!

836
00:30:52,390 --> 00:30:54,669
Didn't you say Dad
only had three months left?

837
00:30:54,670 --> 00:30:56,319
So you want to take those three months?

838
00:30:56,320 --> 00:30:57,669
With your attitude,

839
00:30:57,670 --> 00:30:59,839
you'd drive him to the grave in a day.

840
00:30:59,840 --> 00:31:01,759
Give it a rest! One month for her?

841
00:31:01,760 --> 00:31:02,629
Look.

842
00:31:02,630 --> 00:31:04,519
I'll handle the first three months.

843
00:31:04,520 --> 00:31:06,559
Okay, I get it now.

844
00:31:06,560 --> 00:31:08,750
None of you can live without him.

845
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:09,519
Is that it?

846
00:31:09,520 --> 00:31:10,600
- Right.
- Right.

847
00:31:10,840 --> 00:31:11,799
Good.

848
00:31:11,800 --> 00:31:13,750
Such brotherly love.

849
00:31:14,230 --> 00:31:15,039
Such family devotion.

850
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:16,030
Yes.

851
00:31:16,560 --> 00:31:18,709
- A truly moving display of love.
- It really is.

852
00:31:18,710 --> 00:31:20,559
You're family.

853
00:31:20,560 --> 00:31:22,600
Nobody wants to let him down, right?

854
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:23,599
Good.

855
00:31:23,600 --> 00:31:25,640
Everyone, stay right here.

856
00:31:25,880 --> 00:31:26,799
Wait a moment.

857
00:31:26,800 --> 00:31:28,759
Let your tempers cool.

858
00:31:28,760 --> 00:31:30,559
Tone down the unbridled energy.

859
00:31:30,560 --> 00:31:33,469
I'm going to talk to Mr. Yao alone.

860
00:31:33,470 --> 00:31:34,839
At the end of the day,

861
00:31:34,840 --> 00:31:37,709
we have to honor the ward's own wishes.

862
00:31:37,710 --> 00:31:38,750
Right?

863
00:31:39,360 --> 00:31:40,799
This is a court of law.

864
00:31:40,800 --> 00:31:42,189
Stop shouting.

865
00:31:42,190 --> 00:31:44,230
Keep it down, understood?

866
00:31:45,150 --> 00:31:46,429
Where's the payroll card?

867
00:31:46,430 --> 00:31:46,989
Hand it over.

868
00:31:46,990 --> 00:31:47,629
Shut up!

869
00:31:47,630 --> 00:31:48,189
Where is it?!

870
00:31:48,190 --> 00:31:49,629
I'm not shutting up! Make me!

871
00:31:49,630 --> 00:31:50,559
I'm not shutting up!

872
00:31:50,560 --> 00:31:52,160
I'll shout as loud as I want! So what?

873
00:31:52,300 --> 00:31:53,399
I'll scream if I feel like it!

874
00:31:53,400 --> 00:31:57,680
(Third Floor Hallway)

875
00:32:05,840 --> 00:32:07,270
Mr. Yao.

876
00:32:08,390 --> 00:32:09,389
I'm truly sorry.

877
00:32:09,390 --> 00:32:10,989
Given your physical condition,

878
00:32:10,990 --> 00:32:13,510
we shouldn't have put you
through a trip to court.

879
00:32:13,910 --> 00:32:15,470
Today's situation...

880
00:32:16,470 --> 00:32:18,160
Well, you've seen it for yourself.

881
00:32:18,430 --> 00:32:19,949
Between your relatives here,

882
00:32:19,950 --> 00:32:22,310
there seems to be
no room for compromise.

883
00:32:22,470 --> 00:32:23,989
By the book,

884
00:32:23,990 --> 00:32:25,759
I'm supposed to keep trying to mediate.

885
00:32:25,760 --> 00:32:27,879
If one session fails, we do two.

886
00:32:27,880 --> 00:32:29,880
If two fail, we do three.

887
00:32:29,950 --> 00:32:31,470
But based on experience,

888
00:32:31,880 --> 00:32:33,840
I think it would be a waste of time.

889
00:32:34,190 --> 00:32:34,949
This case

890
00:32:34,950 --> 00:32:37,319
is inevitably headed for a court ruling.

891
00:32:37,320 --> 00:32:39,880
And given your current health,

892
00:32:41,040 --> 00:32:42,880
I don't want to exhaust you any further.

893
00:32:44,630 --> 00:32:47,710
So, while we have this moment today,

894
00:32:47,800 --> 00:32:49,079
could you tell me

895
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:51,510
honestly what you're thinking?

896
00:32:51,910 --> 00:32:53,230
Of the three of them,

897
00:32:53,470 --> 00:32:55,680
who would you prefer to live with?

898
00:32:58,800 --> 00:33:00,120
Mr. Yao?

899
00:33:06,120 --> 00:33:07,400
Mr. Yao?

900
00:33:10,710 --> 00:33:11,990
Mr. Yao!

901
00:33:15,470 --> 00:33:17,440
- Get the medics! Notify the family!
- On it!

902
00:33:19,320 --> 00:33:20,600
Get inside!

903
00:33:21,320 --> 00:33:23,310
What's happening? What happened?!

904
00:33:26,470 --> 00:33:27,389
Dad!

905
00:33:27,390 --> 00:33:28,990
What's wrong? What's going on?!

906
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:29,989
- Dad!
- Brother!

907
00:33:29,990 --> 00:33:31,559
Dad! Are you okay?

908
00:33:31,560 --> 00:33:33,669
- We have an unconscious elder!
- The line's dead!

909
00:33:33,670 --> 00:33:34,949
Send an ambulance immediately!

910
00:33:34,950 --> 00:33:35,469
Honey!

911
00:33:35,470 --> 00:33:36,880
Get him out of here!

912
00:33:37,280 --> 00:33:39,360
What did you do to him?!

913
00:33:39,560 --> 00:33:40,389
Honey!

914
00:33:40,390 --> 00:33:41,909
Dad, are you okay?

915
00:33:41,910 --> 00:33:42,799
Honey!

916
00:33:42,800 --> 00:33:44,119
Help him! Do something!

917
00:33:44,120 --> 00:33:45,710
Look! You have to...

918
00:33:46,150 --> 00:33:47,319
Honey!

919
00:33:47,320 --> 00:33:49,709
How did this happen?! Hurry up!

920
00:33:49,710 --> 00:33:50,920
Honey!

921
00:33:53,800 --> 00:33:55,710
Wait! I'm not in yet.

922
00:33:55,880 --> 00:33:56,559
Wait!

923
00:33:56,560 --> 00:33:57,469
I need to get in.

924
00:33:57,470 --> 00:33:58,839
Only one family member allowed.

925
00:33:58,840 --> 00:34:00,080
Just one of you.

926
00:34:05,760 --> 00:34:06,879
Judge Shen!

927
00:34:06,880 --> 00:34:07,629
What happened?

928
00:34:07,630 --> 00:34:09,069
My brother was fine a moment ago!

929
00:34:09,070 --> 00:34:10,279
How did he end up like this?!

930
00:34:10,280 --> 00:34:11,159
I'm warning you!

931
00:34:11,160 --> 00:34:12,759
If anything happens to my husband,

932
00:34:12,760 --> 00:34:13,759
you will pay for this!

933
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:15,359
If my brother doesn't make it,

934
00:34:15,360 --> 00:34:17,120
I'm coming for all of you!

935
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:27,400
(Emergency)

936
00:34:38,880 --> 00:34:41,080
I was requested a second mediation.

937
00:34:41,110 --> 00:34:42,279
I also told them

938
00:34:42,280 --> 00:34:43,949
to resolve the matter in court.

939
00:34:43,950 --> 00:34:45,350
But I also specified

940
00:34:45,640 --> 00:34:48,520
it should only happen
after his recovery.

941
00:34:49,070 --> 00:34:51,239
But to what degree did he recover?

942
00:34:51,240 --> 00:34:53,520
What medical standards
were actually met?

943
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:55,469
What's the benchmark
for appearing in court?

944
00:34:55,470 --> 00:34:56,549
Is there a doctor's note?

945
00:34:56,550 --> 00:34:57,790
Did you personally

946
00:34:57,950 --> 00:34:59,430
verify this with the physician?

947
00:35:00,200 --> 00:35:01,319
At the time,

948
00:35:01,320 --> 00:35:02,799
the doctor had cleared his discharge.

949
00:35:02,800 --> 00:35:04,879
The family consented,
so we proceeded.

950
00:35:04,880 --> 00:35:06,359
But when he arrived,

951
00:35:06,360 --> 00:35:07,549
he was in a wheelchair

952
00:35:07,550 --> 00:35:09,270
and hooked up to a ventilator.

953
00:35:09,280 --> 00:35:10,429
I understand that,

954
00:35:10,430 --> 00:35:11,759
on the surface,

955
00:35:11,760 --> 00:35:14,029
Mr. Yao's condition
didn't seem fit for a hearing.

956
00:35:14,030 --> 00:35:15,069
But sending him back home

957
00:35:15,070 --> 00:35:16,359
would have been a wasted trip.

958
00:35:16,360 --> 00:35:17,509
Besides, Shen asked for

959
00:35:17,510 --> 00:35:18,909
Mr. Yao's agreement.

960
00:35:18,910 --> 00:35:21,279
He gave his consent before we started.

961
00:35:21,280 --> 00:35:22,549
But had we canceled,

962
00:35:22,550 --> 00:35:24,759
we would have faced severe complaints.

963
00:35:24,760 --> 00:35:26,359
Under those circumstances,

964
00:35:26,360 --> 00:35:28,389
the judge had no safer alternative.

965
00:35:28,390 --> 00:35:30,029
Yet the man died in our court.

966
00:35:30,030 --> 00:35:33,679
Now the family is
demanding five million.

967
00:35:33,680 --> 00:35:34,949
Do you truly believe

968
00:35:34,950 --> 00:35:37,160
you bear no responsibility at all?

969
00:35:37,550 --> 00:35:39,279
The family is exploiting the tragedy.

970
00:35:39,280 --> 00:35:41,239
If the court simply
pays up to keep them quiet

971
00:35:41,240 --> 00:35:42,549
and hush things up,

972
00:35:42,550 --> 00:35:44,870
it's incredibly unfair to our judges.

973
00:35:46,390 --> 00:35:50,350
It seems Ms. Shu is even
more upset than Judge Shen.

974
00:35:50,590 --> 00:35:52,389
Shen hasn't been
in the Family Court long.

975
00:35:52,390 --> 00:35:54,120
He's still learning the ropes.

976
00:35:54,430 --> 00:35:55,359
As his mentor

977
00:35:55,360 --> 00:35:56,389
and the Deputy Chief Judge,

978
00:35:56,390 --> 00:35:58,109
the responsibility lies with me.

979
00:35:58,110 --> 00:35:59,909
We will continue the investigation.

980
00:35:59,910 --> 00:36:01,319
But until then,

981
00:36:01,320 --> 00:36:03,310
I'd prefer not to jump to conclusions.

982
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:15,910
Look.

983
00:36:15,950 --> 00:36:16,759
Shen,

984
00:36:16,760 --> 00:36:18,799
I need you to step back
from your current cases.

985
00:36:18,800 --> 00:36:19,679
Hand them to Ms. Shu

986
00:36:19,680 --> 00:36:21,759
while we wait for the final results.

987
00:36:21,760 --> 00:36:22,960
Is that clear?

988
00:36:24,470 --> 00:36:25,589
Yes.

989
00:36:25,590 --> 00:36:27,310
I accept the court's decision.

990
00:36:27,950 --> 00:36:30,109
Judge Shen really
had a run with bad luck.

991
00:36:30,110 --> 00:36:31,359
The old man was on his deathbed.

992
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:32,639
He even needed a ventilator!

993
00:36:32,640 --> 00:36:34,239
And yet the family dragged him to court.

994
00:36:34,240 --> 00:36:35,359
Exactly.

995
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:36,759
Now the family is trying to pin

996
00:36:36,760 --> 00:36:37,879
the whole thing on the court.

997
00:36:37,880 --> 00:36:39,549
Judge Shen was
minding his own business

998
00:36:39,550 --> 00:36:41,160
when this mess hit him.

999
00:36:41,320 --> 00:36:42,029
He's going to be

1000
00:36:42,030 --> 00:36:43,589
dragged through the mud for a while.

1001
00:36:43,590 --> 00:36:44,839
He's been in there for ages.

1002
00:36:44,840 --> 00:36:46,390
That can't be a good sign.

1003
00:36:46,530 --> 00:36:47,589
What now?

1004
00:36:47,590 --> 00:36:49,270
Quiet! Judge Shen is back.

1005
00:36:50,160 --> 00:36:51,359
Judge Shen! How did it go?

1006
00:36:51,360 --> 00:36:52,830
What did the investigation team say?

1007
00:36:53,640 --> 00:36:54,759
Not much.

1008
00:36:54,760 --> 00:36:56,750
They just told me
to wait for the results.

1009
00:36:58,880 --> 00:37:00,430
Wait, what's going on?

1010
00:37:05,760 --> 00:37:07,080
Hey, what's the deal?

1011
00:37:07,240 --> 00:37:08,109
What's the status?

1012
00:37:08,110 --> 00:37:08,949
Suspended or fired?

1013
00:37:08,950 --> 00:37:10,429
Come on, spill it!

1014
00:37:10,430 --> 00:37:11,719
Yeah, give us the scoop!

1015
00:37:11,720 --> 00:37:12,759
Tell us!

1016
00:37:12,760 --> 00:37:14,040
Ms. Shu...

1017
00:37:14,200 --> 00:37:15,520
was a total badass.

1018
00:37:28,910 --> 00:37:30,430
What are you looking at?

1019
00:37:33,880 --> 00:37:35,679
Listen, what you just did in there

1020
00:37:35,680 --> 00:37:37,109
was way too impulsive.

1021
00:37:37,110 --> 00:37:38,350
Think about it.

1022
00:37:42,110 --> 00:37:44,199
You only needed to state the facts

1023
00:37:44,200 --> 00:37:45,469
to the investigators.

1024
00:37:45,470 --> 00:37:46,109
Right?

1025
00:37:46,110 --> 00:37:47,949
You weren't supposed
to give your opinion.

1026
00:37:47,950 --> 00:37:49,549
You're Shen's mentor.

1027
00:37:49,550 --> 00:37:51,239
We need to keep our cool here.

1028
00:37:51,240 --> 00:37:52,909
It's because I'm his mentor

1029
00:37:52,910 --> 00:37:55,319
that I should be speaking up about this.

1030
00:37:55,320 --> 00:37:57,040
I wasn't making excuses for him.

1031
00:37:57,380 --> 00:37:59,509
Doing that only gives the investigators

1032
00:37:59,510 --> 00:38:01,639
a negative impression of Shen.

1033
00:38:01,640 --> 00:38:02,319
Think about it.

1034
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:03,799
Defending him like that

1035
00:38:03,800 --> 00:38:05,159
in front of everyone?

1036
00:38:05,160 --> 00:38:07,549
The team saw exactly
what you were doing.

1037
00:38:07,550 --> 00:38:10,109
It's only going
to skew their judgment of him.

1038
00:38:10,110 --> 00:38:12,200
Was I supposed to just stay silent?

1039
00:38:12,910 --> 00:38:15,120
Ms. Shu, Chief Judge He
wants to see you.

1040
00:38:21,070 --> 00:38:21,909
Have some water.

1041
00:38:21,910 --> 00:38:23,000
Thanks.

1042
00:38:23,470 --> 00:38:24,600
You...

1043
00:38:24,990 --> 00:38:26,799
You shouldn't have been so hot-headed.

1044
00:38:26,800 --> 00:38:28,719
Nothing has been officially decided yet.

1045
00:38:28,720 --> 00:38:31,239
The investigation team is here
to gather the facts.

1046
00:38:31,240 --> 00:38:32,429
And look at you.

1047
00:38:32,430 --> 00:38:33,759
You went in there looking for a fight.

1048
00:38:33,760 --> 00:38:35,429
They were acting like vultures.

1049
00:38:35,430 --> 00:38:36,589
How could I not step in?

1050
00:38:36,590 --> 00:38:38,199
The higher-ups know

1051
00:38:38,200 --> 00:38:39,679
how difficult our position is.

1052
00:38:39,680 --> 00:38:41,279
We're already drowning in our own work.

1053
00:38:41,280 --> 00:38:42,639
Who would go out of their way

1054
00:38:42,640 --> 00:38:44,199
to force a man hooked up to tubes

1055
00:38:44,200 --> 00:38:45,029
to come to court?

1056
00:38:45,030 --> 00:38:47,199
It's not that the higher-ups
don't understand

1057
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:49,199
the challenges we face
on the front lines.

1058
00:38:49,200 --> 00:38:51,199
But an investigation team

1059
00:38:51,200 --> 00:38:52,719
is not a support group.

1060
00:38:52,720 --> 00:38:55,230
Their questioning has to
be objective and impartial.

1061
00:38:55,240 --> 00:38:57,870
They're splitting hairs over
the "fitness to stand" protocol.

1062
00:38:57,910 --> 00:38:58,989
When that call was made,

1063
00:38:58,990 --> 00:39:00,239
we were all right there.

1064
00:39:00,240 --> 00:39:01,759
No one stepped in to stop it, right?

1065
00:39:01,760 --> 00:39:03,109
Xiezhi miscalculated

1066
00:39:03,110 --> 00:39:05,199
the old man's health
and what he could handle.

1067
00:39:05,200 --> 00:39:06,719
But as he said,

1068
00:39:06,720 --> 00:39:08,469
the family is the one at fault.

1069
00:39:08,470 --> 00:39:10,799
They literally pushed
him into the court.

1070
00:39:10,800 --> 00:39:11,989
How could we not mediate?

1071
00:39:11,990 --> 00:39:13,029
If we'd refused,

1072
00:39:13,030 --> 00:39:14,589
we would've been reported anyway.

1073
00:39:14,590 --> 00:39:16,109
They'd have called us bureaucratic

1074
00:39:16,110 --> 00:39:17,480
and made it difficult.

1075
00:39:17,880 --> 00:39:18,719
True.

1076
00:39:18,720 --> 00:39:20,640
Even that would be better than this.

1077
00:39:20,680 --> 00:39:22,350
But who could've foreseen this?

1078
00:39:24,070 --> 00:39:24,909
Enough.

1079
00:39:24,910 --> 00:39:26,719
When will the autopsy report be ready?

1080
00:39:26,720 --> 00:39:28,040
The day after tomorrow, likely.

1081
00:39:31,030 --> 00:39:32,310
If it turns out

1082
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:35,589
Mr. Yao's death was caused
by oxygen deprivation,

1083
00:39:35,590 --> 00:39:37,719
then we just need to prove

1084
00:39:37,720 --> 00:39:39,279
the tube came loose by accident,

1085
00:39:39,280 --> 00:39:41,509
or that he pulled it out himself.

1086
00:39:41,510 --> 00:39:43,040
I've checked with the hospital.

1087
00:39:43,110 --> 00:39:44,719
Given how these machines are made,

1088
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:46,509
it was most likely suicide.

1089
00:39:46,510 --> 00:39:48,469
Did you see the way they were acting?

1090
00:39:48,470 --> 00:39:50,319
The family was making a total scene.

1091
00:39:50,320 --> 00:39:51,600
If I were in his shoes,

1092
00:39:51,680 --> 00:39:53,109
I wouldn't want to live either.

1093
00:39:53,110 --> 00:39:55,429
The only thing that matters
is the evidence.

1094
00:39:55,430 --> 00:39:56,989
Yes, evidence is key.

1095
00:39:56,990 --> 00:39:58,909
Whether they charge him with murder

1096
00:39:58,910 --> 00:40:00,680
or negligent homicide,

1097
00:40:00,760 --> 00:40:02,640
the fault lies with them.

1098
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:06,040
Don't forget,

1099
00:40:06,240 --> 00:40:08,359
it's not like we're just dealing

1100
00:40:08,360 --> 00:40:09,239
with the criminal courts.

1101
00:40:09,240 --> 00:40:10,359
We're up against

1102
00:40:10,360 --> 00:40:13,090
netizens who don't
have the full picture.

1103
00:40:13,360 --> 00:40:14,639
I'll find the proof.

1104
00:40:14,640 --> 00:40:16,040
I'll make them shut up.

1105
00:40:17,200 --> 00:40:18,350
Go then.

1106
00:40:23,510 --> 00:40:24,239
This is the view

1107
00:40:24,240 --> 00:40:26,870
from the camera
behind the monitoring room.

1108
00:40:27,550 --> 00:40:28,560
No good.

1109
00:40:28,640 --> 00:40:30,230
Are there any other angles?

1110
00:40:31,640 --> 00:40:33,639
This is from the front camera.

1111
00:40:33,640 --> 00:40:34,429
It's the widest angle,

1112
00:40:34,430 --> 00:40:36,120
but the distance is too great.

1113
00:40:37,030 --> 00:40:38,799
Why is he covered with a blanket?

1114
00:40:38,800 --> 00:40:39,910
Zoom in.

1115
00:40:46,160 --> 00:40:47,430
More.

1116
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:49,040
That's the limit.

1117
00:40:53,880 --> 00:40:55,790
The blanket is blocking everything.

1118
00:40:55,950 --> 00:40:57,679
You can't see any movement at all.

1119
00:40:57,680 --> 00:40:59,069
That's why the family claims

1120
00:40:59,070 --> 00:41:00,989
we're intentionally hiding the truth.

1121
00:41:00,990 --> 00:41:02,509
Look at this footage.

1122
00:41:02,510 --> 00:41:04,469
Judge Shen, Chief Judge He, me,

1123
00:41:04,470 --> 00:41:05,509
and you

1124
00:41:05,510 --> 00:41:06,989
have watched it at least ten times.

1125
00:41:06,990 --> 00:41:07,949
There's simply

1126
00:41:07,950 --> 00:41:10,080
no way we missed anything.

1127
00:41:10,320 --> 00:41:11,109
Is there any way

1128
00:41:11,110 --> 00:41:12,909
to enhance the image quality?

1129
00:41:12,910 --> 00:41:15,350
Maybe see the hand movement
under the blanket?

1130
00:41:16,030 --> 00:41:18,069
That's outside my area of expertise.

1131
00:41:18,070 --> 00:41:19,509
Maybe I should consult a specialist.

1132
00:41:19,510 --> 00:41:20,750
Do it.

1133
00:41:25,110 --> 00:41:26,430
I'm not coming.

1134
00:41:26,950 --> 00:41:28,509
It's nothing.
Why would something be wrong?

1135
00:41:28,510 --> 00:41:30,390
Too many cases, I can't leave.

1136
00:41:30,470 --> 00:41:32,679
And stop using Grandpa as an excuse.

1137
00:41:32,680 --> 00:41:34,429
Grandpa has his own life.

1138
00:41:34,430 --> 00:41:35,949
He won't get dementia

1139
00:41:35,950 --> 00:41:37,830
for not spending time with me.

1140
00:41:38,550 --> 00:41:39,640
Hanging up.

1141
00:41:43,840 --> 00:41:45,949
I was just speaking casually.

1142
00:41:45,950 --> 00:41:48,239
If he's busy and can't come back,
then so be it.

1143
00:41:48,240 --> 00:41:49,109
Besides,

1144
00:41:49,110 --> 00:41:50,989
I have plenty of people to see

1145
00:41:50,990 --> 00:41:52,560
and plenty of things to do.

1146
00:41:52,640 --> 00:41:53,790
In a bit,

1147
00:41:54,030 --> 00:41:56,000
I'll just head out
for a stroll by myself.

1148
00:41:57,200 --> 00:41:59,040
That little brat...

1149
00:42:00,200 --> 00:42:01,310
I understand.

1150
00:42:01,360 --> 00:42:01,909
But,

1151
00:42:01,910 --> 00:42:04,390
he has to pay the price
for his own actions.

1152
00:42:07,840 --> 00:42:08,949
I'm hanging up now.

1153
00:42:08,950 --> 00:42:10,120
Okay, okay.

1154
00:42:12,200 --> 00:42:13,790
What happened this time?

1155
00:42:14,320 --> 00:42:16,120
Why the sudden rush?

1156
00:42:18,240 --> 00:42:20,589
Shen Xiezhi isn't coming back this week.

1157
00:42:20,590 --> 00:42:22,359
Shouldn't you ask him

1158
00:42:22,360 --> 00:42:23,799
what's going on with our son?

1159
00:42:23,800 --> 00:42:25,750
Work at the court is very demanding.

1160
00:42:25,760 --> 00:42:27,870
When Dad was listening,
he actually said

1161
00:42:27,910 --> 00:42:32,000
that seniors who want to play
with grandkids have dementia!

1162
00:42:34,110 --> 00:42:35,679
Xiezhi wouldn't say that.

1163
00:42:35,680 --> 00:42:38,029
Are you twisting his logic
and spreading rumors again?

1164
00:42:38,030 --> 00:42:39,389
It was close enough.

1165
00:42:39,390 --> 00:42:40,960
It sounded pretty nasty.

1166
00:42:41,030 --> 00:42:43,600
Shouldn't you give him a call?

1167
00:42:43,760 --> 00:42:45,069
Look, at the very least,

1168
00:42:45,070 --> 00:42:47,429
a family having one meal
together a week...

1169
00:42:47,430 --> 00:42:49,080
isn't too much to ask.

1170
00:42:49,160 --> 00:42:51,029
Besides, Dad is getting older.

1171
00:42:51,030 --> 00:42:52,589
Fine.

1172
00:42:52,590 --> 00:42:54,390
I'll talk to Dad.

1173
00:42:55,200 --> 00:42:57,600
Xiezhi won't be back for a while.

1174
00:42:57,890 --> 00:42:59,910
No need to call him for now.

1175
00:43:00,200 --> 00:43:01,359
Why not?

1176
00:43:01,360 --> 00:43:02,430
He's busy.

1177
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

1178
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

1179
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

1180
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1181
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1182
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1183
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

1184
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

1185
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

1186
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

1187
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

1188
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1189
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1190
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1191
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

1192
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

1193
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

1194
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

1195
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

1196
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,810
♪To answer those voices♪

1197
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,240
♪You deserve to be happy♪

1198
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,990
♪Loud and clear♪

1199
